import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['rate'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['month_year'] = data['date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m')
    avg_rate = data.groupby(['year', 'month'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='month_year', y='rate', data=avg_rate, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=avg_rate['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average rate')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average rate in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="rate", data=data)
    chart.set_title("What is the frequency of rate values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    chart.axhline(y=data['rate'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max frequency: {:.2f}'.format(data['rate'].value_counts().max()))
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
